1
00:00:00,182 --> 00:00:03,620
They would stand here, their
guard post was in this spot

2
00:00:04,167 --> 00:00:07,578
And when you called him,
he'd come and take you out

3
00:00:09,714 --> 00:00:10,989
Interviewer: And where
are the washbasins?

4
00:00:11,014 --> 00:00:12,109
These are the washbasins

5
00:00:12,134 --> 00:00:13,385
Interviewer: Is this a bathroom?

6
00:00:13,410 --> 00:00:16,146
It's a bathroom, but
there's no showering

7
00:00:17,552 --> 00:00:20,625
They don't let anyone shower

8
00:00:20,650 --> 00:00:22,995
You only go into the toilet

9
00:00:23,020 --> 00:00:24,635
Interviewer: Is the
bathroom in the same place?

10
00:00:24,660 --> 00:00:25,781
The washbasins are here

11
00:00:26,276 --> 00:00:27,813
And here are the
other washbasins

12
00:00:29,922 --> 00:00:32,188
Here we go in, take care
of our needs, and come out

13
00:00:33,620 --> 00:00:35,130
I mean the washbasins
are only here

14
00:00:37,109 --> 00:00:41,068
Interviewer: Were you put under
any pressure when you went in?

15
00:00:41,093 --> 00:00:45,719
No, no, you went in normally
and took the time you needed

16
00:00:49,443 --> 00:00:51,422
Interviewer: Where
did the jailer stand?

17
00:00:51,447 --> 00:00:57,177
He stood here in this spot

18
00:00:58,219 --> 00:01:04,026
We used to
call—<i>hajji</i>, washbasins

19
00:01:04,756 --> 00:01:06,631
He'd come, open the door, and say—Who
wants to go out to the washbasins?

20
00:01:06,656 --> 00:01:08,000
Then he'd take him out

21
00:01:08,704 --> 00:01:12,766
He'd bring the person back once he was done
and ask—Does anyone else want to go in?

22
00:01:13,391 --> 00:01:17,219
Each person was allowed
to go to the washbasins twice

23
00:01:20,656 --> 00:01:23,547
Interviewer: Was
water available?

24
00:01:23,572 --> 00:01:25,162
Yes, it was

25
00:01:29,302 --> 00:01:31,594
Interviewer: How
was the cleanliness?

26
00:01:33,052 --> 00:01:37,713
This chapel was clean

27
00:01:38,308 --> 00:01:41,980
They used to wash it—he'd
hold the water hose and wash

28
00:01:46,094 --> 00:01:53,386
And if no guards were around,
the prisoners cleaned it themselves

29
00:01:55,417 --> 00:01:56,745
I mean they cleaned
in their own spots

30
00:01:57,396 --> 00:01:58,855
I didn't see them

31
00:01:58,880 --> 00:02:02,709
But they said they sometimes
went out and cleaned

32
00:02:03,125 --> 00:02:06,771
That's what the guys who'd
been here more than ten days said

33
00:02:08,672 --> 00:02:11,042
They'd go out to rinse and
clean and then go back inside

34
00:02:11,355 --> 00:02:12,891
They only cleaned the washbasins

35
00:02:13,151 --> 00:02:15,808
The corridors were
clean—there was no dirt

36
00:02:18,587 --> 00:02:22,780
Interviewer: Were people harassed
when they went into the toilet?

37
00:02:22,805 --> 00:02:24,915
Like the jailer banging on
the door to hurry them out?

38
00:02:24,940 --> 00:02:29,056
No, you took your time, finished,
came out, and he put you back inside

39
00:02:30,670 --> 00:02:32,571
Everyone called them <i>hajji</i>

40
00:02:32,596 --> 00:02:35,071
No one used the word ISIS

41
00:02:46,582 --> 00:02:49,420
Interviewer: Have there been
any changes to the place?

42
00:02:49,445 --> 00:02:53,691
The place is the
same—it hasn't changed

43
00:02:56,660 --> 00:03:01,530
Interviewer: Could you go
inside and show us the place?

44
00:03:06,495 --> 00:03:08,084
This is the place

45
00:03:18,448 --> 00:03:19,672
Interviewer: Nothing
has changed in it?

46
00:03:19,776 --> 00:03:21,938
No, it's the same place

47
00:03:22,849 --> 00:03:24,672
Interviewer: Was there
an open window here?

48
00:03:24,698 --> 00:03:26,313
It was closed off
with this metal sheet

49
00:03:27,719 --> 00:03:30,063
Just a spot for ventilation

50
00:03:30,688 --> 00:03:33,865
But the sheet is here
and there's a square gap

51
00:03:33,890 --> 00:03:35,167
Only for ventilation

52
00:03:37,172 --> 00:03:39,542
Interviewer: Haven't you heard
of anyone who tried to escape?

53
00:03:39,567 --> 00:03:40,948
No, no one

54
00:03:46,201 --> 00:03:53,023
Interviewer: We saw some
prisoners go to the toilets

55
00:03:53,048 --> 00:03:55,966
Just so they could sit
by themselves for a bit

56
00:03:56,174 --> 00:04:00,628
Do you know people like that, or did
you yourself try to sit alone for a while?

57
00:04:00,653 --> 00:04:01,799
No, no

58
00:04:03,492 --> 00:04:07,398
People would only relieve
themselves and come back
